description: Trees dot the edge of the lane and the happy trill of songbirds fills the air.  Looking for the source of the song, you spot a brightly plumaged bird perched on a branch, singing loudly, proclaiming his territory to all other avians in the vicinity.

Trees dot the edge of the lane and a soft series of hoots fills the air.  Looking for the source of the song, you spot a large, white, snowy owl perched on a branch, proclaiming his territory to all other avians in the vicinity.
title: [Temple Burrow, Oleani Way]
